defaultf (indeed, the thrust of the committee’s questions does raise con
defaultcerns that the committee 
defaulthas allowed itself to be misled in this regard).
default&#xa0;
default4. 
defaultHaving been involved in three IPCC assessment cycles, I do not see that the measures taken since the 2007 report 
defaulthave significantly altered the robustness of core conclusions
default, 
defaultbecause these were already
default as robust as any scientific assessment process could make them. The committee should be aware that the importance of errors in previous assessments has been wildly ex
defaultaggerated. 
