defaultth
default Assessment, both of which provided evidence for a downward revision of the uncertainty range for climate sensitivity. A third paper, providing evidence 
defaultfor a higher value for climate sensitivity, was accepted two days later, and hence could not be included. The fact that the first two papers and not the third contribute to the 
defaultofficial 
defaultconsensus view on climate sensitivity for the next six years is clearl
defaulty absurd.
