default&#xa0;
default10. The most obvious and important area 
defaultin which further effort is required to reduce uncertainty is the implications of these global changes for regional climate and extreme weather events. It is shameful, in my view, that we are still unable as a community to quantify the role of human influen
defaultce on high-impact 
defaultevents like Typhoon Haiyan. The IPCC process may inadvertently have contributed to this situation through its focus (mandated by the commissioning governments) on long-term projections of global climate change, which are necessarily relia
defaultnt on coarse-resolution models.
